news.title: HDFC sells 2.4% shares in Ansal Housing
news.para: This transaction includes sale of 6,24,000 shares representing 1.05% of the paid-up share capital of Ansal Housing done on November 30, 2022.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso owner says will go for another audit before taking down buildings
news.para: It said it has had preliminary discussions with the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) and Engineers India Limited (EIL) for another structural audit in order to get a second opinion.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 18-acre land parcel in Kandivali, Mumbai
news.para: The project will have a developable potential of approximately 3.72 million sq ft with an estimated revenue potential of approximately Rs 7,000 crore.

news.title: Mangaluru city corporation to refloat tenders for LED streetlights project
news.para: Since the project failed to achieve at least 20% progress, even after many deadline extensions, the city corporation has decided to invite tenders again, to install 60,000 LED streetlights in the city.

news.title: Blox raises nearly Rs 100 crore from investors
news.para: The company is planning to utilize the funds raised for market expansion, boosting the product portfolio, and building data infrastructure across customers, brokers, and developer segments.

news.title: Navi Mumbai metro project receives Rs 500 crore credit from ICICI Bank
news.para: "City and Industrial Development Corporation (CIDCO) signed an agreement for the industrial line of credit for Rs 500 crore with the Industrial Credit and Investment Corporation of India (ICICI). With this, the financial closure process for the metro line no. 1 project has been completed," CIDCO said in a release.

news.title: Haryana shehri vikas pradhikaran's settlement scheme ends, allottees may go to HC
news.para: HSVP authorities have decided to discontinue the scheme. At the same time, some of the allottees from Panchkula have now decided to challenge the enhanced rates and arrears added with the OTS scheme before the high court for intervention and relief.

news.title: Madras HC restrains illegal brick kilns in Tuticorin district
news.para: A division bench of justice R Mahadevan and justice J Sathya Narayana Prasad directed the authorities to take action if the brick kilns are functioning without proper licence.

news.title: Ahmedabad: NOC from ASI needed to regularize construction near protected monuments
news.para: This is prerequisite for properties located within the 100m-radius prohibited area or 300m-radius restricted buffer area of an ASI protected monument in the Walled City.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board tweaks law for offering turnkey houses to owners
news.para: Now, whatever new independent houses or multi-storeyed flats will be built by the Housing Board for different income groups, they will be built on the basis of these new types of designs.

news.title: Dharwad: HDMC mulls bringing two lakh hidden properties under ambit of civic tax
news.para: Opening the discussion on increasing the revenue, senior corporator Veeranna Savadi fumed at officials for their poor show in tax collection.

news.title: CRDA Act amendment to make use of PMAY: Andhra Pradesh government to HC
news.para: Arguing on behalf of the state government, additional advocate general P Sudhakar Reddy said the Union government will give funds for construction of houses and the state government intends to construct houses apart from giving house sites to the landless poor in capital city.

news.title: Noida: There are over 300 flats in sector 117, but no park to visit
news.para: Taking cognisance of the residents' demand, Noida authority CEO Ritu Maheshwari directed the chief architect planner (CAP) for a detailed report of the issue and the area and assured action based on the report.

news.title: Rajasthan government lowers max height cap for buildings on small plots
news.para: Effectively these changes concentrated on reducing the maximum permissible limit of heights for new buildings to be built on small plots measuring up to 750 square metre.

news.title: Bulldozers at Raisina Hills, two years after NGT order to restore forest
news.para: Gurgaon’s divisional forest officer Rajiv Tejyan said that a total of 52 violations were reported in areas protected under sections 4 and 5 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA), 1900. “Showcause notices have been issued to all the violators. More demolitions are to follow in the coming days.”
